div.p:
He repreſents to them that they had nothing to do to Judge or Cenſure their Brethren; 

                  Ver. 4. & ſeq.
                for they were God's Servants, and to Him only they ſtood or fell; that though they were miſtaken in their Notions as to the Points in Controverſie, yet nevertheleſs, if what was done upon thoſe miſtaken Principles, was done out of a pure heart, and as in obedience to the Commands of God, it would be accepted of him.
